    "summary": "All 7 records are real, correctly-named installation/construction vessels with physically plausible crane SWLs, dimensions, and deck data for their vessel types. Web spot-checks confirmed headline numbers on 6 records: Sleipnir (2x10,000t @48m, tandem 20,000t, 220x102m), Saipem 7000 (2x7,000t, tandem 14,000t @42m, 198x87m), Pioneering Spirit (48,000t topsides / 25,000t jacket, 382x124m), Seven Borealis (5,000t Huisman crane, 5,500 m2 deck, 350/10 t/m2, 182.2x46.2m), BokaLift 2 (4,000t Huisman crane, 231x49m, 7,500 m2 deck, fly jib 125m, year 2000), and Thialf crane/dims (tandem 14,200t, 201.6x88.4m). No fabrication: every hard number carries an on-topic citation (Ship-Technology, Wikipedia, SWZ Maritime, Marine Insight, MarineTraffic) and unpublished figures are honestly marked 'gap'. The dataset transparently discloses that brochure PDFs were search-extracted, not parsed (access=brochure-pdf). TWO factual IMO lookup errors found (not fabrications): Thialf listed as IMO 8757537 but the real IMO is 8757740; Saipem 7000 listed as IMO 8757501 but the real IMO is 8501567 (the dataset itself already flags 'confirmed IMO number' as a gap for Saipem 7000). These IMOs should be corrected before use; all other data stands.",
